TITLE: Rendering a Basic Custom Edge using React Flow (JSX)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a functional React component for a custom edge that draws a straight SVG path between two nodes using React Flow utilities. Requires the '@xyflow/react' package and expects props for edge id, source and target coordinates. The BaseEdge is rendered with the computed straight path; this snippet provides the foundation for further edge customization via edge types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/xyflow/web/blob/main/sites/reactflow.dev/src/content/learn/customization/custom-edges.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { BaseEdge, getStraightPath } from '@xyflow/react';\n\nexport default function CustomEdge({ id, sourceX, sourceY, targetX, targetY }) {\n  const [edgePath] = getStraightPath({\n    sourceX,\n    sourceY,\n    targetX,\n    targetY,\n  });\n\n  return (\n    <>\n      <BaseEdge id={id} path={edgePath} />\n    </>\n  );\n}
```

