TITLE: Applying the `nodrag` Utility Class in a Custom Node (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates adding the `nodrag` CSS class to an input element within a custom React Flow node component (written in TSX). This prevents the node dragging behavior when the user interacts with the input element, allowing standard input interaction like text selection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/xyflow/web/blob/main/sites/reactflow.dev/src/content/learn/customization/custom-nodes.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
export default function CustomNode(props: NodeProps) {
  return (
    <div>
      <input className="nodrag" type="range" min={0} max={100} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

