TITLE: Defining a Custom Mind Map Edge for React Flow - TSX
DESCRIPTION: This TSX snippet creates a custom edge component for React Flow that renders a straight edge between two nodes using the BaseEdge and getStraightPath utilities from the @xyflow/react package. It receives standard edge properties (sourceX, sourceY, targetX, targetY), computes a straight SVG path, and passes all props into BaseEdge. Dependencies include @xyflow/react. Inputs are edge coordinates, and the output is a React component rendering the edge. Limitations: only supports straight paths.
SOURCE: https://github.com/xyflow/web/blob/main/sites/reactflow.dev/src/content/learn/tutorials/mind-map-app-with-react-flow.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { BaseEdge, EdgeProps, getStraightPath } from '@xyflow/react';

function MindMapEdge(props: EdgeProps) {
  const { sourceX, sourceY, targetX, targetY } = props;

  const [edgePath] = getStraightPath({
    sourceX,
    sourceY,
    targetX,
    targetY,
  });

  return <BaseEdge path={edgePath} {...props} />;
}

export default MindMapEdge;
```

