TITLE: Handling Node Deletion in React Flow to Recover Connections
DESCRIPTION: This code implements a solution for maintaining flow connections when a middle node is deleted. It uses onNodesDelete callback to detect node deletion, then utilizes getConnectedEdges, getIncomers, and getOutgoers utility functions to identify and reconnect the affected nodes, creating new edges that bypass the deleted node.
SOURCE: https://github.com/xyflow/web/blob/main/apps/example-apps/react/examples/nodes/delete-middle-node/README.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
const onNodesDelete = useCallback(
  (deleted) => {
    setEdges((edges) => {
      // Get all the edges that are not connected to the deleted nodes
      const remainingEdges = edges.filter(
        (edge) =>
          !deleted.some(
            (node) => node.id === edge.source || node.id === edge.target
          )
      );

      // For each deleted node, and for each pair of incoming and outgoing edges,
      // create a new edge that connects the source of the incoming edge with the
      // target of the outgoing edge.
      const createdEdges = deleted.flatMap((deletedNode) => {
        const incomers = getIncomers(deletedNode, nodes, edges);
        const outgoers = getOutgoers(deletedNode, nodes, edges);

        return incomers.flatMap(({ id: source }) =>
          outgoers.map(({ id: target }) => ({
            id: `${source}->${target}`,
            source,
            target,
          }))
        );
      });

      return [...remainingEdges, ...createdEdges];
    });
  },
  [nodes]
);
```

