TITLE: Computing Bezier Edge Paths with @xyflow/react - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to use getBezierPath from @xyflow/react to compute SVG path data and geometry information required to render a Bezier curve between two nodes. Dependencies include the @xyflow/react package and access to the Position enum. Parameters specify positions and directions for the source and target nodes, and the function returns a tuple with the SVG path string and label coordinates/offsets. Outputs are demonstrated with console logs, showing the calculated coordinates and path string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/xyflow/web/blob/main/sites/reactflow.dev/src/content/api-reference/utils/get-bezier-path.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { Position, getBezierPath } from '@xyflow/react';

const source = { x: 0, y: 20 };
const target = { x: 150, y: 100 };

const [path, labelX, labelY, offsetX, offsetY] = getBezierPath({
  sourceX: source.x,
  sourceY: source.y,
  sourcePosition: Position.Right,
  targetX: target.x,
  targetY: target.y,
  targetPosition: Position.Left,
});

console.log(path); //=> "M0,20 C75,20 75,100 150,100"
console.log(labelX, labelY); //=> 75, 60
console.log(offsetX, offsetY); //=> 75, 40

```

