TITLE: Defining Custom MindMapEdge Component (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a custom edge component `MindMapEdge` for React Flow. It uses the `getStraightPath` utility function but modifies the `sourceY` coordinate by adding 20 pixels to make the edge appear to originate from the vertical center of the source node, rather than the handle's default position. It renders the calculated path using `BaseEdge`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/xyflow/web/blob/main/sites/reactflow.dev/src/content/learn/tutorials/mind-map-app-with-react-flow.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_26

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
```tsx
import { BaseEdge, EdgeProps, getStraightPath } from '@xyflow/react';

function MindMapEdge(props: EdgeProps) {
  const { sourceX, sourceY, targetX, targetY } = props;

  const [edgePath] = getStraightPath({
    sourceX,
    sourceY: sourceY + 20,
    targetX,
    targetY,
  });

  return <BaseEdge path={edgePath} {...props} />;
}

export default MindMapEdge;
```
