TITLE: Controlling Web Audio Context State (Run/Suspend) in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Provides utility functions to manage the Web Audio `AudioContext`. `isRunning` checks if the context's `state` is currently 'running'. `toggleAudio` asynchronously calls either `context.suspend()` or `context.resume()` based on the current state, returning the resulting Promise. Assumes a `context` variable holding the `AudioContext` instance.
